Generalize this by writing a function that will do this for a given team, and create a tibble with this information for all teams. Arrange this tibble first by winning percentage (descending) and by team (alphabetically) if there are any ties when it comes to winning percentage. A for loop and the add_row() function may be useful here.

summary_stats &lt;- function(team_name, year) {
  ccbga6 |&gt;
    filter(year(mdy(Game_Date)) == year) |&gt; 
    filter(Home_Team == team_name | Away_Team == team_name) |&gt;
    mutate(Outcome = case_when(
      Home_Team == team_name & Score_Difference &gt; 0 ~ "Win",
      Away_Team == team_name & Score_Difference &lt; 0 ~ "Win",
      TRUE ~ "Loss"
    )) |&gt;
    summarize(
      Wins = sum(Outcome == "Win"),
      Losses = sum(Outcome == "Loss"),
      Winning_Percentage = Wins / (Wins + Losses)
    )
}

ccbga10 &lt;- map_dfr(unique(c(ccbga6$Home_Team, ccbga6$Away_Team)), \(team) {
  ccbga6 |&gt;
    filter(Home_Team == team | Away_Team == team) |&gt;
    mutate(Outcome = case_when(Home_Team == team & Score_Difference &gt; 0 ~ "Win", 
                               Away_Team == team & Score_Difference &lt; 0 ~ "Win", 
                               TRUE ~ "Loss")) |&gt;
    summarize(Team = team, Wins = sum(Outcome == "Win"), Losses = sum(Outcome == "Loss"), Winning_Percentage = Wins / (Wins + Losses))}) |&gt; 
  arrange(desc(Winning_Percentage), Team)



